body:
Greetings everyone,

I'm trying to control the Opened and Closed events of the Flyout using Xaml.Behaviors.Avalonia in Avalonia UI 12, but I can't get it to work at all.

My current code is:

<pre><code>
&lt;Button Grid.Column="2" Classes="SubMenu" x:Name="MeuBotao" Margin="4"&gt;
    &lt;StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal"&gt;
        &lt;Image Source="avares://Wamona/Images/SubMenu/Rest/RestAdicionar.png" Width="16" Height="16" Margin="0,0,4,0"/&gt;
        &lt;TextBlock Text="Adicionar" FontWeight="Regular" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,4,0" VerticalAlignment="Center"/&gt;
    &lt;/StackPanel&gt;
    &lt;Button.Flyout&gt;
        &lt;Flyout Placement="Bottom" ShowMode="Transient"&gt;
            &lt;Interaction.Behaviors&gt;
                &lt;EventTriggerBehavior EventName="Opened"&gt;
                    &lt;InvokeCommandAction
                        Command="{Binding CarregarDadosCommand}"
                        CommandParameter="Insumos"
                        PassEventArgsToCommand="True" /&gt;
                &lt;/EventTriggerBehavior&gt;
                &lt;EventTriggerBehavior EventName="Closed"&gt;
                    &lt;InvokeCommandAction
                        Command="{Binding FechadoFlyoutCommand}"
                        PassEventArgsToCommand="True" /&gt;
                &lt;/EventTriggerBehavior&gt;
            &lt;/Interaction.Behaviors&gt;
        &lt;/Flyout&gt;
    &lt;/Button.Flyout&gt;
&lt;/Button&gt;
</code></pre>

In my ViewModel:

<pre><code>
public ReactiveCommand&lt;object, Unit&gt; CarregarDadosCommand { get; }

public ViewModelDialogHostCadatroRestProdutos()
{
    CarregarDadosCommand = ReactiveCommand.CreateFromTask&lt;object&gt;(LoadTempdata, outputScheduler: AvaloniaScheduler.Instance);
}

public async Task LoadTempdata(object type)
{
    if(type == "Insumos")
    {
        await loadInsumos();
    }
    else if (type == "Complementos")
    {
        await LoadComplementos();
    }
}
</code></pre>

Remembering that this same code works normally in Avalonia UI 11 with Avalonia.Xaml.Behaviors.

I tried to follow the sample example:
<pre><code>
&lt;UserControl x:Class="BehaviorsTestApplication.Views.Pages.FlyoutBindingView"
             xmlns="https://github.com/avaloniaui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
             xmlns:vm="using:BehaviorsTestApplication.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:MainWindowViewModel"
             mc:Ignorable="d" d:DesignWidth="600" d:DesignHeight="450"&gt;
  &lt;Design.DataContext&gt;
    &lt;vm:MainWindowViewModel /&gt;
  &lt;/Design.DataContext&gt;
  &lt;StackPanel&gt;
    &lt;Button x:Name="FlyoutButton" Content="Press me"&gt;
      &lt;Button.Flyout&gt;
        &lt;Flyout&gt;
          &lt;TextBox PlaceholderText="Type here"&gt;
            &lt;Interaction.Behaviors&gt;
              &lt;EventTriggerBehavior EventName="TextChanged"&gt;
                &lt;InvokeCommandAction Command="{Binding TextChangedCommand}" PassEventArgsToCommand="True"/&gt;
              &lt;/EventTriggerBehavior&gt;
            &lt;/Interaction.Behaviors&gt;
          &lt;/TextBox&gt;
        &lt;/Flyout&gt;
      &lt;/Button.Flyout&gt;
    &lt;/Button&gt;
    &lt;TextBlock x:Name="GreetingTextBlock"
               Text="{Binding Greeting}"
               HorizontalAlignment="Center"
               VerticalAlignment="Center"/&gt;
  &lt;/StackPanel&gt;
&lt;/UserControl&gt;
</code></pre>

But without success.

Additional info:
- I'm using Xaml.Behaviors version 12.0.0.1
- The EventTriggerBehavior doesn't seem to trigger when the Flyout opens/closes
- I've tried placing Interaction.Behaviors on the Flyout, StackPanel, and Button
- Direct event handlers in code-behind work, but I want to keep it in XAML with MVVM

Can anyone give me a tip or help with this?

Thanks in advance!

